The paper focuses on Natural Language Processing tasks such as sentiment analysis, question type classification, and subjectivity classification, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel neural network architecture, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of pretrained word embeddings and Long Short-Term Memory networks suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The convolutional operators used in the model also suggest a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the analysis of relationships across sentences, which could potentially fall under the scope of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
